.TH "drmm_kmalloc" 9 "drmm_kmalloc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drmm_kmalloc \- &drm_device managed kmalloc()
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void *" drmm_kmalloc
.BI "(struct drm_device *dev "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "gfp_t gfp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
DRM device
.IP "size" 12
size of the memory allocation
.IP "gfp" 12
GFP allocation flags
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is a \fIdrm_device\fP managed version of \fBkmalloc\fP. The allocated memory is
automatically freed on the final \fBdrm_dev_put\fP. Memory can also be freed
before the final \fBdrm_dev_put\fP by calling \fBdrmm_kfree\fP.
